- The integer matrix parameter `grid` must not be null.
- The integer parameters `row` and `col` must be within the bounds of the matrix `grid`.
- The integer parameter `color` must be greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to 1000.
- The integer matrix result is the final grid after coloring the border of the connected component that contains the square `grid[row][col]` with the specified `color`.
- The final grid must maintain the same dimensions as the original grid.
- The final grid must only have the border of the connected component colored with the specified `color`.